commit.message: Optionally truncate SQL query in log, for readability purposes
Clean up thread-local variables after each request
Test runners: run only on latest&greatest Python releases

The old name is still mentioned for laggards still on 1.x.
Fix on_delete

Remove Python 2.7 from Travis tests

I can't get Travis to exclude python 2.x + django 2.x combo
Add required "on_delete" parameter (used to be optional in Django 1.x)
Fix Travis exclude config

Bump version to 1.1, Python req to 3.5 and Django to 1.11

Previous Django releases are officially unsupported by the Django
project. Python 3.5 is the oldest version supported by Django 2.1+

Tweak QUERY_INSPECT_DUPLICATE_MIN to count all duplicate requests

Initial implementation in 61b8f52 used the setting to count only
the duplicates after the first one, which is a bit confusing.

Also added the description to README.
Added new settings to enable logging of tracebacks for non duplicated queries (#26)
Use threading.local to store request_start and conn_queries_len (#28)

Bump version to 1.0.0

As django-queryinspect has been pretty stable (in terms of
changes, at least) for a while, let's make it official and
call it stable software.

Update tests for Python 3.6, and Django 1.10 and 1.11

This also removes tox from Travis builds, as Python 3.5 & 3.6 need
to be explicitly defined for the builds, which makes Travis treat them
as different build environment, which clashes with tox.

Since proper Python/Django compatibility matrix is messy, and to
avoid dozens of Travis builds each time, we simplify it to most recent
(relevant) Python and Django versions.

Full compatibility test run can still be done locally via tox.
